<subSubSection id="C32D4CCFFFF7FFCDFF02EF18FEC0FDE7" pageId="2" pageNumber="283" type="type_taxon">
<paragraph id="8B881F44FFF7FFCDFF02EF18FEC0FDE7" blockId="2.[136,778,569,620]" pageId="2" pageNumber="283">
<emphasis id="B943C356FFF7FFCDFF02EF18FEE0FDC7" bold="true" box="[136,303,569,588]" pageId="2" pageNumber="283">
<typeStatus id="548CA1E6FFF7FFCDFF02EF18FF0BFDC7" box="[136,196,569,588]" pageId="2" pageNumber="283">Type</typeStatus>
species.
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C3764C7FFF7FFCDFEB6EF18FDBEFDC7" authorityName="Ferreira &amp; Menezes &amp; Quagio-Grassioto" authorityYear="2011" box="[316,625,569,588]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Characidae" genus="Lepidocharax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="283" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="diamantina">
<emphasis id="B943C356FFF7FFCDFEB6EF18FDBEFDC7" box="[316,625,569,588]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="283">Lepidocharax diamantina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, by original designation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C32D4CCFFFF7FFCDFF02EFB8FB58FEE2" pageId="2" pageNumber="283" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B881F44FFF7FFCDFF02EFB8FDFDFC47" blockId="2.[136,779,665,1100]" pageId="2" pageNumber="283">
<emphasis id="B943C356FFF7FFCDFF02EFB8FF31FD27" bold="true" box="[136,254,665,684]" pageId="2" pageNumber="283">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
According to our analysis, 
<taxonomicName id="4C3764C7FFF7FFCDFDA2EFB8FD71FD27" authorityName="Ferreira &amp; Menezes &amp; Quagio-Grassioto" authorityYear="2011" box="[552,702,665,684]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Characidae" genus="Lepidocharax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="283" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B943C356FFF7FFCDFDA2EFB8FD71FD27" box="[552,702,665,684]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="283">Lepidocharax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be phylogenetically diagnosed from the remaining 
<taxonomicName id="4C3764C7FFF7FFCDFD0EEF98FCC5FD47" baseAuthorityName="Menezes &amp; Weitzman" baseAuthorityYear="2009" box="[644,778,697,716]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Characidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="283" phylum="Chordata" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Stevardiinae">Stevardiinae</taxonomicName>
by the presence of the following autapomorphies supporting clade 4: 1) parhypural and hypural 1 either contacting each other leaving a narrow joint line between them or fused to each other (character 64, state 1), and 2) nasal tubular, without bone expansion (character 96, state 1). Both characters are, however, homoplastically shared among other 
<taxonomicName id="4C3764C7FFF7FFCDFDF7EE58FCC8FC07" baseAuthorityName="Menezes &amp; Weitzman" baseAuthorityYear="2009" box="[637,775,889,908]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Characidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="283" phylum="Chordata" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Stevardiinae">Stevardiinae</taxonomicName>
. Character 64 (state1) also supports clades 10 and 13, and character 96 (state 1) supports clade 16.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B881F44FFF7FFCDFF24EEF8FB58FEE2" blockId="2.[136,779,665,1100]" lastBlockId="2.[816,1460,182,361]" pageId="2" pageNumber="283">
In addition, several distinguishing features are useful to diagnose 
<taxonomicName id="4C3764C7FFF7FFCDFF65EED8FE4AFB87" authorityName="Ferreira &amp; Menezes &amp; Quagio-Grassioto" authorityYear="2011" box="[239,389,1017,1036]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Characidae" genus="Lepidocharax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="283" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B943C356FFF7FFCDFF65EED8FE4AFB87" box="[239,389,1017,1036]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="283">Lepidocharax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It can be distinguished from all the other genera of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C3764C7FFF7FFCDFE0FE938FDD3FBA7" baseAuthorityName="Menezes &amp; Weitzman" baseAuthorityYear="2009" box="[389,540,1049,1068]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Characidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="283" phylum="Chordata" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Stevardiinae">Stevardiinae</taxonomicName>
except 
<taxonomicName id="4C3764C7FFF7FFCDFD09E938FCCDFBA7" authorityName="Bohlke" authorityYear="1954" box="[643,770,1049,1068]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Planaltina" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="2" pageNumber="283" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B943C356FFF7FFCDFD09E938FCCDFBA7" box="[643,770,1049,1068]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="283">Planaltina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C3764C7FFF7FFCDFF02E918FE94FBC7" authorityName="Perugia" authorityYear="1891" box="[136,347,1081,1100]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Characidae" genus="Pseudocorynopoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="283" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B943C356FFF7FFCDFF02E918FE94FBC7" box="[136,347,1081,1100]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="283">Pseudocorynopoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C3764C7FFF7FFCDFE18E918FDE5FBC7" box="[402,554,1081,1100]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Characidae" genus="Xenurobrycon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="283" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B943C356FFF7FFCDFE18E918FDE5FBC7" box="[402,554,1081,1100]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="283">Xenurobrycon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having the dorsalfin origin on the same vertical crossing the anal-fin origin. The presence of adnate scales over the ventral caudal-fin lobe distinguishes 
<taxonomicName id="4C3764C7FFF7FFCDFBADEDD7FB00FE82" authorityName="Ferreira &amp; Menezes &amp; Quagio-Grassioto" authorityYear="2011" box="[1063,1231,246,265]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Characidae" genus="Lepidocharax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="283" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B943C356FFF7FFCDFBADEDD7FB00FE82" box="[1063,1231,246,265]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="283">Lepidocharax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName id="4C3764C7FFF7FFCDFAA3EDD7FA65FE82" authorityName="Bohlke" authorityYear="1954" box="[1321,1450,246,265]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Planaltina" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="2" pageNumber="283" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B943C356FFF7FFCDFAA3EDD7FA65FE82" box="[1321,1450,246,265]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="283">Planaltina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C3764C7FFF7FFCDFCBAEC37FBCAFEA2" authorityName="Perugia" authorityYear="1891" box="[816,1029,278,297]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Characidae" genus="Pseudocorynopoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="283" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B943C356FFF7FFCDFCBAEC37FBCAFEA2" box="[816,1029,278,297]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="283">Pseudocorynopoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C3764C7FFF7FFCDFBB4EC37FB17FEA2" box="[1086,1240,278,297]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Characidae" genus="Xenurobrycon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="283" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B943C356FFF7FFCDFBB4EC37FB17FEA2" box="[1086,1240,278,297]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="283">Xenurobrycon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which have a caudal organ or pouch bordered by modified scales or represented by a single modified pouch scale.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C32D4CCFFFF7FFCDFCBAECB7FA6AFDA2" pageId="2" pageNumber="283" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B881F44FFF7FFCDFCBAECB7FA6AFDA2" blockId="2.[816,1459,406,553]" pageId="2" pageNumber="283">
<emphasis id="B943C356FFF7FFCDFCBAECB7FC7DFE22" bold="true" box="[816,946,406,425]" pageId="2" pageNumber="283">Etymology.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B943C356FFF7FFCDFC30ECB7FBCAFE22" box="[954,1029,406,425]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="283">Lepido</emphasis>
, from the Greek, for scales and 
<emphasis id="B943C356FFF7FFCDFAE2ECB7FA7CFE22" box="[1384,1459,406,425]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="283">charax</emphasis>
,from the Greek 
<emphasis id="B943C356FFF7FFCDFC51EC97FBFDFE42" box="[987,1074,438,457]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="283">characo</emphasis>
, meaning pointed stake, here used in reference to the characid genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C3764C7FFF7FFCDFB1EECF7FB2AFE62" box="[1172,1253,470,489]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Characidae" genus="Charax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="283" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B943C356FFF7FFCDFB1EECF7FB2AFE62" box="[1172,1253,470,489]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="283">Charax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, hence a Characid fish. 
<taxonomicName id="4C3764C7FFF7FFCDFCEDECD7FC32FD82" authorityName="Ferreira &amp; Menezes &amp; Quagio-Grassioto" authorityYear="2011" box="[871,1021,502,521]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Characidae" genus="Lepidocharax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="283" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B943C356FFF7FFCDFCEDECD7FC32FD82" box="[871,1021,502,521]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="283">Lepidocharax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a name used in reference to the scales covering the ventral caudal-fin lobe. A noun in apposition.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
